\begin{definition}
A square matrix $A$ is called reducible if there exists a permutation matrix $P$ such that $$PAP^{t} = \begin{pmatrix}
    A_1 & * \\
    0 & A_2 \\
\end{pmatrix}$$ for some non-trivial square matrices $A_1$ and $A_2.$    
\end{definition}

