perturbations.original:
\begin{definition}
 \cite{HCEV18} A real matrix $A =(a_{i,j})$ is called an almost non-singular $M$-matrix if $A$ is a $Z$-matrix, all its proper principal minors are positive and its determinant is non-negative.    
\end{definition}

